  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Migraine is a condition thought to be related to cortical hyperexcitability. Repetitive
      transcranial magnetic stimulation (rTMS) can modulate the cortical excitability by means of
      long-term potentiation or long-term depression. This study will will test the safety and
      efficacy of rTMS in the treatment of patients with Migraine.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
